When an Important Change has Been Made
Once you have made a change you want to add in
open Git tab in top right
click on staged buttons of changed docs
click commit button (tick in a box)
add a commit message
Click Commit

After a Few Important Commits
Pull first using Blue Arrow
  this confirms that starting point is up to date
Then back out and click the green up arrow to push

When working on Non-R Files
Open Git Bash Cmd Line
Commit:
git commit --message "Include Message Here"
Push:
git push <Repo name> main
Pull:
git pull --ff-only
